155–Deceased","1150–1192":"1150–1192","1185–1205":"1185–1205","1155–Female":"1155–Deceased","1205":"1205","1155":"1155","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1192":"1192","Riding, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","South Tynedale, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Tindale, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Johanna","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["feminine form of <i>Johannes</i> (  see  John  )."],"variants":[{"name":"Johannah","meanings":["feminine form of <i>Johannes</i> (  see  John  )."]},{"name":"Jonna","meanings":["contracted form of   Johanna ."]},{"name":"Jane","meanings":["Originally a feminine form of   John  , from the Old French form <i>Je(h)anne</i>. Since the 17th century it has proved the most popular of the feminine forms of <i>John</i>, ahead of   Joan   and   Jean .  It now also commonly occurs as the second element in combinations such as <i>Sarah-Jane</i>. In Britain it is still one of the most frequent of all girls' names. It is not a royal name, but was borne by the tragic  Lady Jane Grey  (  1537–54 ), who was unwillingly proclaimed queen in  1553 , deposed nine days later, and executed the following year. Seventy years earlier, the name had come into prominence as that of  Jane Shore , mistress of  King Edward IV  and subsequently of  Thomas Grey , 1st Marquess of Dorset, Lady Jane's grandfather. Jane Shore's tribulations in  1483  at the hands of  Richard III , Edward's brother and successor, became the subject of popular ballads and plays, which may well have increased the currency of the name in the 16th century. A 19th-century influence was its use as the name of the central character in  Charlotte Brontë's  novel Jane Eyre (  1847 ). From  1932 to 1959  it was used as the name of a cheerful and scantily clad beauty whose adventures were chronicled in a strip cartoon in the Daily Mirror. It is also borne by the American film stars  Jane Russell  (  1921–2011 ) and  Jane Fonda  (  b. 1937 )."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Johanna was born in 1155, in Northumberland, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Baron Adam II de Tyndall."},"et":{"1155–":"1155–Surnud","1150–1192":"1150–1192","1185–1205":"1185–1205","1155–Female":"1155–Surnud","1205":"1205","1155":"1155","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1192":"1192","Riding, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","South Tynedale, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Tindale, Northumberland, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1155–":"1155–Kuollut","1150–1192":"1150–1192","1185–1205":"1185–1205","1155–Female":"1155–Kuollut","1205":"1205","1155":"1155","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1192":"1192","Riding, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","South Tynedale, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Tindale, Northumberland, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1155–":"1155–Décédée","1150–1192":"1150–1192","1185–1205":"1185–1205","1155–Female":"1155–Décédée","1205":"1205","1155":"1155","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1192":"1192","Riding, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","South Tynedale, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Tindale, Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Johanna est née en 1155, à Northumberland, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Elle a eu au moins 1 fille avec Baron Adam II de Tyndall."},"de":{"1155–":"1155–Verstorben","1150–1192":"1150–1192","1185–1205":"1185–1205","1155–Female":"1155–Verstorben","1205":"1205","1155":"1155","1185":"1185","1150":"1150","1192":"1192","Riding, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","South Tynedale, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom":"Tindale, Northumberland, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Johanna wurde 1155 in Northu